QuestionText: Which of the following best describes the Liskov Substitution Principle in object-oriented programming?
OptionA: Derived classes must use methods from base classes.
OptionB: Objects of a superclass should be replaceable with objects of subclasses without altering desirable properties.
OptionC: Subclass constructors must call superclass constructors.
OptionD: Superclasses should implement all methods found in their subclasses.
CorrectAnswer: Objects of a superclass should be replaceable with objects of subclasses without altering desirable properties.

QuestionText: In C++, which type of inheritance can lead to the ‘diamond problem’?
What is the primary purpose of method overloading in object-oriented programming?
OptionA: Allow a subclass to override parent methods.
OptionB: Permit multiple methods with the same name, differentiated by parameter types or count.
CorrectAnswer: Permit multiple methods with the same name, differentiated by parameter types or count.

QuestionText: Which design pattern provides an interface for creating families of related or dependent objects without specifying their concrete classes?
In Java, which keyword prevents a class from being inherited?
Which of the following violates the principle of encapsulation?
OptionA: Making all class data members public.
CorrectAnswer: Making all class data members public.

QuestionText: Which concept allows objects to decide at runtime which method implementation to invoke?
If a subclass in Java overrides a parent method but changes the return type to an incompatible type, what occurs?
Which of the following statements about C# interfaces is TRUE?
OptionC: A class can implement multiple interfaces.
OptionD: Interfaces can provide default method implementations.
CorrectAnswer: A class can implement multiple interfaces.
